The paper discusses Internet topology analysis, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions interdisciplinary cross-fertilization, which suggests that it may be relevant to other subfields such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
